Problem Statement

You are given a permutation p of length n and an integer m. You construct a directed graph from this permutation.
An edge exists directed from index i to index j if:
1. p[i] < p[j] (the value at the starting node is strictly less than the value at the destination node)
2. abs(i - j) <= k (the distance between their indices in the array is at most k)

Find the minimum value of k such that the longest path of the resulting graph has a length greater than or equal to m.
Note: The length of the path is equal to the number of nodes in that path.

Constraints
1 <= n <= 10^5
1 <= m <= n
1 <= p[i] <= n

